Privacy Policy

Thank you for using our application. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, store, and protect user's personal information when using our software. By using the application, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

Information Collection
Our application does not collect personal data or send information to third parties. We do not require an internet connection, and we do not use cookies.

Use of Information
The main purpose of our application is to process images from your device's camera or image gallery. The images are processed locally on your device and are not sent or stored on our servers. The processing results may be saved to the internal storage of your device for your convenience only.

Storage of Information
The processed images by the application may be stored locally on the internal storage of your device. These images are not accessible by us or any third parties unless you choose to manually share them through other applications or services.

Security Responsibility
Since our application does not collect or send any personal information, the security of data is the user's responsibility. It is important for you to take appropriate measures to protect your device and ensure the security of the stored information.

Changes to this Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy periodically. We recommend that you review this policy regularly to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.

Contact
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the use of our application, please contact us at the following email address: thales.l.a.valente@gmail.com and jdallyson@nca.ufma.br.

By using our application, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

